<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
The species occurs primarily in the area of southwestern Tanzania north of lake Nyassa, and also in eastern Zambia, Ndola, Oct 1906, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="51" start="start">C</pageBreakToken>
.F.E. Allen 363
</emphasis>
(SRGH). 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, CE" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" refId="B11" refString="Smith, CE, 1971. Observations on Stengelioid Species of Vernonia. Agricultural Handbook No. 396, U. S. Department of Agriculture, i-iv, 1-87." title="Observations on Stengelioid Species of Vernonia. Agricultural Handbook No. 396, U. S. Department of Agriculture, i-iv, 1 - 87." year="1971">Smith (1971)</bibRefCitation>
cited an outlying population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robinson &amp; Skvarla" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Robinson &amp; Skvarla" baseAuthorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyassae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Vernonia nyassae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Transvaal (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Codd &amp; Winter 3291</emphasis>
, K). Examination of the voucher specimen at Kew shows that it belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Phillips" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thodei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Vernonia thodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Phillips (now in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Robinson, J.Skvarla &amp; V.A.Funk" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pseudopegolettia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Pseudopegolettia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H. Rob., Skvarla &amp; Funk, in prep.), a totally distinct entity with a different non-lophate form of pollen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<bibRefCitation author="Jeffrey, C" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="195 - 277" publicationUrl="10.2307/4113734" refId="B7" refString="Jeffrey, C, 1988. The Vernonieae in East Tropical Africa. Kew Bulletin 43 (2): 195 - 277, 10.2307/4113734" title="The Vernonieae in East Tropical Africa." url="10.2307/4113734" volume="43" year="1988">Jeffrey (1988)</bibRefCitation>
cited a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robinson &amp; Skvarla" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Robinson &amp; Skvarla" baseAuthorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyassae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Vernonia nyassae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the region T4, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Bally 7496</emphasis>
, from Ugalla R. (K), which is &quot;smaller than specimens from T7 in all floral parts; it may be simply depauperate, or may indicate a populational difference.&quot;
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, CE" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" refId="B11" refString="Smith, CE, 1971. Observations on Stengelioid Species of Vernonia. Agricultural Handbook No. 396, U. S. Department of Agriculture, i-iv, 1-87." title="Observations on Stengelioid Species of Vernonia. Agricultural Handbook No. 396, U. S. Department of Agriculture, i-iv, 1 - 87." year="1971">Smith (1971)</bibRefCitation>
cited the following specimens as seen from within the range of the species: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Tanzania:</emphasis>
Sao Hill, 6200 feet, Feb 1959, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">A.M. Watermeyer 32</emphasis>
(K). Mbeya Distr., Slopes of Mbeya Mt., 9000 feet, 25 Sep 1936, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">B.D. Burtt 6331</emphasis>
(K). Southern Highlands Prov., Njombe Distr., Elton Plateau, 8500 feet, 6 Oct 1954, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">R.L. Willan 172</emphasis>
(K). Near Njombe, 2100 m, 17 Jan 1957, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">H.M. Richards 7874</emphasis>
(K). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Zambia:</emphasis>
Highlands, Ndola, Oct 1906, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">C.F.E. Allen 363</emphasis>
(SRGH).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
